The Ooni of Ife, Oba Adeyeye Enitan Ogunwusi, yesterday, honoured 100 youths with Royal African Young Leadership Forum award and promised to keep encouraging and motivating youths. The event which was held at the Oduduwa Hall of the Obafemi Awolowo University (OAU), Ile-Ife, was attended by dignitaries including the Minister of Youth and Sports, Mr Sunday Dare. Oba Ogunwusi charged the recipients to keep adding value to themselves and make Africa and the black proud of them. He also urged them to be good role models for other youths coming behind them. 